[{"id":"VR857495","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the top view of two blocks labeled Block 1 and Block 2. Each block is semicircular and the two blocks are positioned together to form a circular shape with Block 1 on the left and Block 2 on the right. A laser beam moving down and to the right enters Block 1 at a right angle to its surface and continues down and to the right to point P, which is the center of the circular shape produced by both blocks. The laser beam makes angle theta sub 1 with a horizontal dash line crossing point P. After crossing the boundary, the laser beam changes direction and moves down and to the right at angle labeled theta sub 2 relative to the horizontal dash line, where theta sub 2 is greater than theta sub 1. The beam then exits Block 2 at a right angle to the surface. The original path of the laser beam from Block 1 through point P continues beyond point P as a dashed line through a point outside Block 2 labeled Q.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857495.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure shows a top view of two semicircular, transparent blocks of equal size, Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, that have been placed in contact with each other. Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> has an index of refraction <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub 1\"><math alttext=\"n sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> has an index of refraction <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub 2\"><math alttext=\"n sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>. A laser beam is directed into Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and is incident on the interface between the blocks at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span>, the common center of the two blocks. At Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span>, the incident beam makes an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> from the normal to the interface and is refracted into Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>, where it makes an angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 2\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> with the normal. Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math></span></span> is at a location that the beam would intersect if the blocks were not present. Which of the following actions <span class=\"formatted_text text_decoration:underline\">could</span> result in the beam intersecting Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857495_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Making the angle of incidence at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span> greater than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub 1\"><math alttext=\"theta sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Replacing Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> with an identically-sized block that has an index of refraction greater than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub 1\"><math alttext=\"n sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Replacing Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> with an identically-sized block in which light travels slower than it does in Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Swapping the positions of blocks <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]